ball_team\", \"score\": 0.999981700598344, \"rank\": 1.770390908015201e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Hamby was added lateas an injury replacementfor Cameron Brink.)\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dearica_Hamby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dearica_Hamby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dearica_Hamby\"}, {\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Brink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cameron Brink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Brink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Brink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jimmer Fredette, Dylan Travis, Kareem Maddox and Canyon Barry will play for Team USA on the men's side.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1320, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmer Fredette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\", \"score\": 0.9999999654255595, \"rank\": 1.775566059714531e-08, \"text\": \"Dylan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\"}, {\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"score\": 0.565618070154322, \"rank\": 0.7679774616405216, \"text\": \"Travis\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9959370555371391, \"rank\": 0.004079142486079942, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}, {\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999981700598344, \"rank\": 1.770390908015201e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A game of 3x3 basketball is played on a half court with both teams\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094made up of four players (three on the court and one reserve)\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094defending and attacking the same hoop.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To win, a team must have the most points after 10 minutes of play or be the first team to reach 21 points.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A shot beyond the perimeter is worth two points in 3x3 basketball, while a basket inside the arc is worth one point.\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eight teams will compete for the gold medal in both the men's and women's 3x3 basketball tournament.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All teams will play seven games, matching up against the other countries in the pool play round.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams will then be ranked based on their records.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After pool play, the top two teams advance to the semifinals, while the bottom two teams are eliminated.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The remaining four teams will compete in a play-in round (No.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"3 seed vs. No.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"6 seed; No.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"4 seed vs. No.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"5 seed) to determine the other two semifinalists.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics will host every 3x3 matchup for both the men's and women's tournaments at La Concorde, an open arena located in the heart of the city.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympics will be broadcast live by NBC and its other properties, including USA Network, CNBC, E!\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999714679461729, \"rank\": 2.8352516426780648e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2563, \"end\": 2574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.9997220101714397, \"rank\": 0.0002780671285957245, \"text\": \"USA Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}, {\"begin\": 2576, \"end\": 2580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999463079817, \"rank\": 5.369211246767031e-08, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"and the streaming platform Peacock.\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every 3x3 basketball game\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094from the round robin part of the tournament to the gold medal game\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094will be streamed live on Peacock, but NBC will also air games live over local NBC affiliates as well as E!, CNBC and USA Network.\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2743, \"end\": 2750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999998651173974, \"rank\": 1.3482999969713916e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 2756, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999714679461729, \"rank\": 2.8352516426780648e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999714679461729, \"rank\": 2.8352516426780648e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2826, \"end\": 2830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999463079817, \"rank\": 5.369211246767031e-08, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2835, \"end\": 2846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.9997220101714397, \"rank\": 0.0002780671285957245, \"text\": \"USA Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q2